        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I didn't want to add a custom validators and decided to override my form's isValid() instead. Doing my custom logic there was straightforward, except that I couldn't set the errors on my elements as they are managed internally by Zend_Form_Element with no public accessors.\n\nI propose that we add public accessors for errors and messages. It makes sense regardless of the use case I demonstrated."
        },
